Reasoning: The paper deals with the achievable rate region of a collaborative coding scheme in a pairwise network, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of decode and forward coding and the study of the rate trade-off suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the consideration of channel conditions and the numerical results suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of computer engineering (cs.CE).
